result.execSummary:
The defendant Denard R Aikens was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: No use or possession of alchol or controlled substances, except for those prescribed by treating health care provider.  Random testing as requested by supervising agent.  Cooperate with AODA assessment and follow through with treatment, counseling and program recommendation, including aftercare.

Provider DNA sample if not previously provided.  Pay DNA surcharge.  Cooperate with treatment, counseling and programs determined appropriate.  Follow through with recommendations.  Voting prohibited until sentence has been completed and civil rights are restored.  Firearm prohibition warning given.
